<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-11T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-11T03:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8951:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-11T11:00:00+03:00">March 11, 1941—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>42. British Ambassador confirms information Hare’s number 107.<note n="13" xml:id="d495fn13"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note>
                                Eden stressed rupture relations with Italy and told Suwaidi he would
                                expect hear something definite this regard on his return London and
                                intimated British help Iraq if action favorable. If not favorable
                                Ambassador says further economic pressure will be exerted.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>